# REPO TRUTH — READ BEFORE TOUCHING ANYTHING

This is the JARVIS project. A governed Iron Man-style AI command center.
Running on Windows machine 10.0.0.249.

## Services and ports (REAL, DEPLOYED)
- Control plane: FastAPI, port 8001 (source of truth for mission state)
- Voice server: FastAPI + WebSocket, port 8000
- OpenClaw gateway: port 18789
- Command Center: React/Vite, port 5173 (ACTIVE, replaces Mission Control)
- LobsterBoard: port 8080
- DashClaw: https://jarvis-dashclaw.vercel.app (permanent, Neon PostgreSQL)
- Ollama (Qwen 3.5 4B): port 11434
- PostgreSQL + Redis: Docker

## Event flow (canonical)
voice → jarvis.commands → control plane → jarvis.execution → executor worker → jarvis.receipts → control plane → jarvis.updates → voice + Command Center

## What is MISSING (do not assume it exists)
- Executor worker (reads jarvis.execution, does webbrowser.open, etc.) — NOT BUILT
- Three-zone Command Center layout — NOT DONE
- Wake word / conversation memory on voice — NOT DONE
- Test suite — DOES NOT EXIST
- Process supervision / auto-restart — DOES NOT EXIST

## What is DEPRECATED (do not touch)
- Mission Control (ports 3000/3001) — being killed, replaced by Command Center (5173)

## RULES
1. Inspect actual files before any changes.
2. Ask to see file content if uncertain.
3. Do not rebuild working services.
4. One slice at a time. Do not change multiple services at once.
5. After writing code, verify against this truth file.
6. Models: local = Qwen 3.5 4B via Ollama. cloud = MiniMax 2.5.
7. Stack: FastAPI, SQLModel, Redis, PostgreSQL, React/Vite, pyttsx3, faster-whisper, pystray.